"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100118","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-24","<p>In 2010/11 Government funding for VisitBritain and VisitEngland was £40.323 million. In 2014/15 Government funding was £51.984 million. The table contains a breakdown of the funding:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>VisitBritain GIA (£m)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>VisitBritain GREAT Funding (£m)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>VisitEngland GIA (£m)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>VisitEngland GREAT Funding (£m)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>VisitEngland Regional Growth Fund via BIS (£m)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>40.323*</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>40.323</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>19.883</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>6.364</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>6.737</p></td><td><p>51.984</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*grant-in-aid for both bodies was recorded on a consolidated basis before 2011/12.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-24T12:43:25.5416684Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100118/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100118/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100118/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-10-21","VisitBritain and VisitEngland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the core funding for VisitBritain and VisitEngland was in 2010 and is now.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","211285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100119","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-28","<p>The Northern Ireland Minister for Culture Arts and Leisure has not raised this matter with me. Questions surrounding the funding of the Ulster Orchestra are matters for the Northern Ireland Executive.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-10-28T09:40:46.0178803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100119/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100119/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100119/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-10-21","Orchestras: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions he has had with Northern Ireland's Minister for Culture, Arts and Leisure on the future of the Ulster Orchestra.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","211218"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100120","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-24","<p>Since 2010, domestic tourism spend in England has grown by 14.1% - from £56.7bn* to £64.7bn in 2013. Domestic tourism spend in 2012 was a record-breaking £67,956m. We will not have a final figure for 2014 until next year. Overall, Deloitte estimated that the tourism industry was worth £127 billion GVA to the UK economy in 2013, £58 billion of which is ‘direct’ contribution.</p><p> </p><p><em>Source: </em><a href="http://www.visitengland.org/insight-statistics/major-tourism-surveys/overnightvisitors/" target="_blank"><em>http://www.visitengland.org/insight-statistics/major-tourism-surveys/overnightvisitors/</em></a><em> ; </em><a href="http://www.visitengland.org/insight-statistics/major-tourism-surveys/dayvisitors/" target="_blank"><em>http://www.visitengland.org/insight-statistics/major-tourism-surveys/dayvisitors/</em></a></p><p>*this is based on an estimate as there was no day visit survey in 2010</p><p> </p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-24T12:41:38.9195595Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100120/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100120/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-10-21","Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the value to the economy of domestic tourism was in (a) 2012, (b) 2013 and (c) 2014.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","211253"
